# watchdog.env.example — config template for scripts/ops/prod-watchdog.sh
#
# Copy to /home/deploy/production/watchdog.env on the PROD box (49.12.233.2) and
# `chmod 600` it. prod-watchdog.sh sources this file explicitly, which is how it
# stays cron-safe: cron does NOT load shell-profile vars, so push-alert secrets
# must live here, not in ~/.bashrc / ~/.profile.
#
# All values are optional — the script has sane defaults matching the repo.
# Uncomment + fill what you need.

# Slack push alerts (opt-in). Empty = no Slack (stdout->MAILTO + syslog still fire).
# SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL="https://hooks.slack.com/services/XXX/YYY/ZZZ"

# Dead-man's-switch (opt-in but RECOMMENDED). The script pings this URL on every
# healthy run and "<url>/fail" on failure; the external monitor (healthchecks.io,
# UptimeRobot heartbeat, Better Uptime, ...) alarms if the pings ever STOP —
# catching the case where the cron / box / script itself dies.
# HEARTBEAT_URL="https://hc-ping.com/<uuid>"

# Override only if needed (defaults shown):
# APP_CONTAINER="nestjs-remix-monorepo-prod"
# CADDY_CONTAINER="nestjs-remix-caddy"
# EXPECTED_IMAGE="massdoc/nestjs-remix-monorepo:production"
# PUBLIC_HEALTH_URL="https://www.automecanik.com/health"
# WATCHDOG_LOG="/tmp/prod-watchdog.log"
# EXEC_TIMEOUT="15"
# CURL_TIMEOUT="10"
